'''Chumig Gyatsa''' is one of the 24 Buddhist [[vajrayana|Tantric]] places.
Chumig Gyatsa means 'Hundred Waters' in [[Standard Tibetan|Tibetan]]. It is the local name for the pilgrimage site [[Muktinath]], a sacred place both for [[Hindus]] as well as the [[Buddhists]], located at an [[altitude]] of 3,710 meters, at the foot of the Thorung La mountain pass (part of the [[Himalayas]]), [[Mustang (kingdom)|Mustang district]], [[Nepal]].
==External links== *[http://www.muktinath.org/muktinath/ Backgrounds on Muktinath-Chumig Gyatsa]
