{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = Gilbert Blaize Rego | title = Bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh|Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh]] (emeritus) | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh|Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh]] | term = 1971 - 1999 | predecessor = Alfred Fernández | successor = Gerald John Mathias <!-- Orders --> | ordination = 3 December 1953 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1921|9|3}} | birth_place = [[Mumbai, India]] [[File:Flag of India.svg|25px]] | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2012|6|21|1921|9|3}} | death_place = Mumbai, India | previous_post = Prelate }}
'''Gilbert Blaize Rego''' (3 September 1921 &ndash; 21 June 2012) was an [[India]]n [[Prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].
Rego was born in [[Mumbai]] and was ordained a priest on 3 December 1953. Rego was appointed bishop to the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh|Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh]] on 11 March 1971 and ordained bishop on 11 September 1971. Rego retired on 10 November 1999 as bishop of the Chandigarh and Simla Diocese.
