{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}} {{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> |image = Phil Pringle.jpg |imagesize = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1952|5|21}} |occupation = Author, [[Evangelism|evangelist]], [[Bible|Bible teacher]], artist |genre = [[Christian]] |spouse = [[Christine Pringle]] |children = Rebekah, Daniel, Joseph }}
'''Philip Andrew "Phil" Pringle''' [[Order of Australia|OAM]]<ref>[http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=877893&search_type=simple&showInd=true Australian Honour Roll]</ref> (born 21 May 1952) is a New Zealand-born [[Australia]]n Christian evangelist. Pringle arrived in [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]], from Christchurch in 1980 with his wife Chris.<ref>http://www2.myc3church.net/phil-pringle</ref><ref>http://philpringle.com/about-phil-pringle</ref><ref>http://www.citynews.sg/2014/03/interview-with-the-blonde-nana-how-mr-and-mrs-pringle-met/</ref> He is the senior pastor of C3 Church Sydney (formerly known as Christian City Church), which was started in a surf club in [[Dee Why, New South Wales|Dee Why]] before moving to a large, rented warehouse,<ref>Pringle, Phil (2003). ''Faith''. PaX Ministries Pty Ltd (p.ii).</ref> after an initial attempt at [[church planting|planting a church]] in the Sydney suburb of [[Roseville, New South Wales|Roseville]].<ref>{{cite book | last= Barclay | first= John | title = Arise | publisher = Covenant Publishing | year= 1987}}</ref> He is the founder of C3 Church Global, a church planting movement.<ref>http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/desire-to-help-puts-new-life-into-churches/2007/05/18/1178995411717.html</ref> He is also the founder and president of [[Oxford Falls Grammar School]], Sydney.<ref>{{cite book | last = Barcay | first = John | title = Arise! The Story of Christian City Church. | publisher = Covenant Publishing | year = 1987}}</ref>
Pringle is an advisory pastor of [[City Harvest Church]] in [[Singapore]] and a long-time friend and mentor of that organisation's leader, [[Kong Hee]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citynews.sg/2013/05/an-interview-with-phil-pringle-chc-has-a-future-of-incredible-blessing/ |title= An Interview with Phil Pringle |author= Theresa Tan |year=2013 |accessdate= }}</ref> Pringle is a member of the board of directors of Dr Yongii Cho's organisation "Church Growth International." <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www2.myc3church.net/phil-pringle/ |title= Phil Pringle |author= |year= |accessdate= }}</ref>
